definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  (1R,5S)-carveol + NAD(+) -eq- (S)-carvone + H(+) + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3beta-hydroxy-5beta-pregnane-20-one + NADP(+) -eq- 5beta-pregnan-3,20-dione + H(+) + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3beta-hydroxy-5alpha-pregnane-20-one + NADP(+) -eq- 5alpha-pregnane-3,20-dione + H(+) + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GDP-6-deoxy-D-mannose + NAD(P)+ -eq- GDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-D-mannose + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2'-deoxymugineic acid + NAD(P)+ -eq- 3''-deamino-3''-oxonicotianamine + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reactions -  isocitrate + NAD+ -eq- 2-oxoglutarate + CO2 + NADH, and (1R,2S)-1-hydroxybutane-1,2,4-tricarboxylate + NAD+ -eq- 2-oxoadipate + CO2 + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-arabinitol + NADP+ -eq- D-ribulose + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-phospho-D-erythronate + NAD(+) -eq- (R)-3-hydroxy-2-oxo-4-phosphonooxybutanoate + H(+) + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1,5-anhydro-D-mannitol + NADP(+) -eq- 1,5-anhydro-D-fructose + H(+) + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  choline + O2 -eq- betaine aldehyde + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  O(2) + secondary alcohol -eq- H(2)O(2) + ketone.

Catalysis of the reactions -  inosine + O2 -eq- 9-riburonosylhypoxanthine + 2 H2O -  (1a) 2 inosine + O2 -eq- 2 5'-dehydroinosine + 2 H2O, and (1b) 2 5'-dehydroinosine + O2 -eq- 2 9-riburonosylhypoxanthine + 2 H2O.

Catalysis of the reactions -  adenosine + 2 O2 -eq- 9-riburonosyladenine + 2 hydrogen peroxide -  (1a) adenosine + O2 -eq- 5'-dehydroadenosine + hydrogen peroxide, and (1b) 5'-dehydroadenosine + O2 -eq- 9-riburonosyladenine + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-gluconate + acceptor -eq- 2-dehydro-D-gluconate + reduced acceptor.

Catalysis of the reactions -  pyranose + acceptor -eq- 2-dehydropyranose (or 3-dehydropyranose or 2,3-didehydropyranose) + reduced acceptor, and a pyranoside + acceptor -eq- a 3-dehydropyranoside (or 3,4-didehydropyranoside) + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a (2R)-hydroxy-carboxylate + acceptor -eq- a 2-oxo-carboxylate + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-2-hydroxy-2-phenylacetate + acceptor -eq- 2-oxo-2-phenylacetate + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  an aldehyde + NADP+ + H2O -eq- an acid + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-oxopropanoate + NAD(P)+ + H2O -eq- malonate + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  fluoroacetaldehyde + NAD+ + H2O -eq- fluoroacetate + NADH + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  an aldehyde + H2O + 2 oxidized ferredoxin -eq- an acid + 2 H+ + 2 reduced ferredoxin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  an aldehyde + H2O + acceptor -eq- a carboxylate + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  chlorophyllide a + NADP+ -eq- divinyl chlorophyllide a + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a flavan-3-ol + 2 NAD(P)+ -eq- an anthocyanidin + 2 NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-arogenate + NADP+ -eq- L-tyrosine + NADPH + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-arogenate + NAD(P)+ -eq- L-tyrosine + NAD(P)H + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  6-(2-amino-2-carboxyethyl)-7,8-dioxo-1,2,3,4,7,8-hexahydroquinoline-2,4-dicarboxylate + 3 O(2) -eq- 2 H(2)O + 2 H(2)O(2) + H(+) + pyrroloquinoline quinone.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-2-benzylsuccinyl-CoA + 2 electron-transferring flavoprotein -eq- (E)-2-benzylidenesuccinyl-CoA + 2 reduced electron-transferring flavoprotein.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-aspartate + H2O + NAD(P)+ -eq- oxaloacetate + NH3 + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-lysine + H(2)O + O(2) -eq- allysine + H(2)O(2) + NH(4)(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-pyrroline + NAD+ + 2 H2O -eq- 4-aminobutanoate + NADH + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-methyltetrahydrofolate + oxidized ferredoxin -eq- 5,10-methylenetetrahydrofolate + reduced ferredoxin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  7-aminomethyl-7-deazaguanine + 2 NADP(+) -eq- 7-cyano-7-deazaguanine + 3 H(+) + 2 NADPH.
Catalysis of the reactions -  hydroxylamine + NH3 -eq- hydrazine + H2O, and hydrazine + acceptor -eq- N2 + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  AMP + glutathione disulfide + H(+) + sulfite -eq- 5'-adenylyl sulfate + 2 glutathione.

Catalysis of the reaction -  peptide-L-methionine + H(2)O + thioredoxin disulfide -eq- peptide-L-methionine (R)-S-oxide + thioredoxin. Can act on oxidized methionine in peptide linkage with specificity for the R enantiomer. Thioredoxin disulfide is the oxidized form of thioredoxin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-methionine + thioredoxin disulfide + H2O -eq- L-methionine (S)-S-oxide + thioredoxin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-methionine + thioredoxin disulfide + H2O -eq- L-methionine (R)-S-oxide + thioredoxin.
Catalysis of the removal of a methyl group from arginine at position 2 of the histone H3 protein.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H2 + A -eq- AH2.
Catalysis of the removal of a methyl group from arginine at position 3 of the histone H4 protein.
Catalysis of the reaction -  linoleate + O2 -eq- (9Z,12Z)-(7S,8S)-dihydroxyoctadeca-9,12-dienoate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  pentane-2,4-dione + O2 -eq- acetate + 2-oxopropanal.

Catalysis of the reaction -  tryptophan + O2 -eq- N-formylkynurenine. The product of the reaction depends on the substrate -  D-tryptophan produces N-formyl-D-kynurenine, and L-tryptophan produces N-formyl-L-kynurenine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4 sulfur + 4 H2O + O2 -eq- 2 hydrogen sulfide + 2 bisulfite + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  Oplophorus luciferin + O2 -eq- oxidized Oplophorus luciferin + CO2 + hnu.
Catalysis of the reaction -  sucrose + acceptor -eq- 3-dehydro-alpha-D-glucosyl-beta-D-fructofuranoside + reduced acceptor.

Catalysis of the reactions -  deoxyamidinoproclavaminate + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 -eq- amidinoproclavaminate + succinate + CO2 + H2O -  proclavaminate + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 -eq- dihydroclavaminate + succinate + CO2 + 2 H2O -  and dihydroclavaminate + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 -eq- clavaminate + succinate + CO2 + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a flavanone + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 -eq- a flavone + succinate + CO2 + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2'-deoxymugineate + 2-oxoglutarate + O(2) -eq- CO(2) + H(+) + mugineate + succinate.
